NAME
     litafa - convert an _a_f_a  from   bit-wise  representation  to
     literal representation

SYNOPSIS
     litafa bitafa

     litafa < bitafa

DESCRIPTION
     litafa reads in a given _a_f_a which is in bit-wise representa-
     tion,  converts  it  to  the   _a_f_a  which  is in its literal
     representation, and then write the _l_i_t_e_r_a_l_i_z_e_d  _a_f_a  on  the
     standard output.

     _b_i_t_a_f_a must conform to the Grail bit-wise format for  alter-
     nating finite state machines.

EXAMPLES
          % cat bitafa2
          symbols: [a,b,c]
          states:  3
          finals:  2
          head: 7 4
          6 2+7 1
          7 1
          0 1
          0 1
          6 2+7 1
          0 1
          0 1
          0 1
          7 3


          % litafa bitafa2
          symbols: [a,b,c]
          states: 3
          finals: q2
          head: ~q1~q2q3
          q2~q3+q1~q2~q3
          q1~q2~q3
          0
          0
          q2~q3+q1~q2~q3
          0
          0
          0
          q1q2~q3

          % litafa < bitafa2
          symbols: [a,b,c]



